SIMPLE: spleenful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spleenful
<hw>Spleen"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Displaying, or
affected with, spleen; angry; fretful; melancholy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Myself have calmed their <qex>spleenful</qex> mutiny.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then rode Geraint, a little <qex>spleenful</qex> yet,⟦br⟧
Across the bridge that spann'd the dry ravine.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spleenish</ent>⟦br⟧
